1.  **(R1) 64-bit Signed IDs:** All IDs are handled as `long`. To prevent precision loss in JSON-parsing environments, IDs are serialized as Strings.
2.  **(R2) Out-of-Order Arrival:** Events are indexed by their internal timestamp in a `TreeMap`, ensuring they are queryable in order regardless of arrival sequence.
3.  **(R3) Silent Duplicate Rejection:** If an ID has already been accepted, subsequent attempts to append it are ignored without error.
4.  **(R4) Non-monotonic Clock Resilience:** The system makes no assumptions about the direction of system time; timestamps are treated as discrete values in a sorted index.
5.  **(F1) Range Querying:** Added the ability to retrieve all events within a `[start, end]` inclusive timestamp range.
6.  **(F2) Event Subscription:** Added a pub/sub mechanism to notify callers of newly accepted (non-duplicate, non-tombstoned) events.
